---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContentImage from '../../components/ContentImage.astro';
import nightCollectionTrap from '../../assets/images/cane-toad-night-collection.png';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cane Toad Trap Guide: What Works and How to Use Traps Safely"
  description="Cane toad trap guide for Florida homeowners. Learn realistic trap performance, safe placement, and how traps fit into a full cane toad control plan."
>
  <div class="urgency">
    <strong>⚠️ Have pets?</strong> Traps help, but they are not emergency protection.
    <a href="/cane-toad-dog-poisoning/">Read emergency protocol →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Cane Toad Traps: What Actually Works</h1>
    <p>Traps can reduce activity when used consistently, but they work best as part of a broader strategy that includes habitat reduction and, in many cases, professional removal.</p>
    <a href="/cane-toad-removal/" class="btn btn-lg">Compare Professional Options →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h2>What Traps Can and Cannot Do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Helpful for ongoing pressure reduction.</li>
      <li>Less effective as a standalone fix on high-density properties.</li>
      <li>Require regular placement checks and maintenance.</li>
    </ul>

    <figure class="content-figure">
      <ContentImage
        src={nightCollectionTrap}
        alt="Nighttime cane toad activity along a Florida yard — traps are most relevant when combined with inspection and habitat control"
      />
      <figcaption>Traps supplement—not replace—consistent night checks, attractant reduction, and professional removal when pressure is high.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>Best Placement Areas</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Near known movement paths along fences and hedges</li>
      <li>Near moisture zones and water-adjacent landscaping</li>
      <li>Away from frequent pet activity areas</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Using too few traps for lot size</li>
      <li>Ignoring attractants like food bowls and lights</li>
      <li>Expecting immediate zero-toad results</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>When to Upgrade to Professional Service</h2>
    <p>If your property sees nightly activity or you have high pet risk, traps alone are usually insufficient. A professional cleanup and maintenance plan is often faster and safer.</p>
    <p>Already seeing toads? <a href="/cane-toad-removal/">Connect with a removal pro →</a></p>

    <p>For the broader picture, visit <a href="/cane-toad-florida/">Cane Toad Florida →</a>.</p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
